1:
Praise Yahweh.\q Praise Yahweh, my soul.
\q
2:
I give praise to Yahweh with all my life;\q I will sing praises to my God as long as I exist.


\q
3:
Do not put your trust in princes\q or in mankind, in whom there is no salvation.
\q
4:
When a person's life's breath stops, he returns to the ground;\q on that day his plans end.


\q
5:
Blessed is he who has the God of Jacob for his help,\q whose hope is in Yahweh his God.
\q
9:
Yahweh protects the foreigners in the land;\q he lifts up the fatherless and widow,
\q but he opposes the wicked.
\q
10:
Yahweh will reign forever,\q your God, Zion, for all generations.
\q Praise Yahweh.
